description.narrative: In 2021;UNICEF enhanced the positioning of the National Girls’ Empowerment Initiative, Dawwie and scaled up community dialogue interventions in partnership with Faith-based Organizations resulting in 53,000 community members engaged in viewing clubs focusing on harmful practices, 55,000 community members engaged face-to-face and over 60,000 online with Dawwie activities. Over 9,000 boys and girls have been trained face-to-face and 3,300 online, on digital literacy focusing on gender equality. UNICEF campaigning on FGM, Safer Internet (AmaniDotCom), Social Inclusion (DiverseButUnited) and Dawwie on its social media platforms, reached 44 million users and engaged with 4 million users. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/12/2021
